{"questionId":"23340","questionHtml":"<p>The orbital radius of Titan around Saturn is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> and the period of revolution is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>R</mi><mrow><mo> </mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math>&nbsp;is the mass of Saturn.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>correct equating of gravitational force / acceleration to centripetal force / acceleration&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>correct rearrangement to reach the expression given&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow use of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;for <strong>MP1</strong>.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"23340","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.6b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The orbital radius of Titan around Saturn is R and the period of revolution is T. Show that T2=4π2R 3GM where M is the mass of Saturn.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation","6.2 – Newton’s law of gravitation","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}